reviews.review_text: I'm going where those chilly winds don't blow Very nice sound on this one..Listen to They Love Each Other and how Phil gets on it..I really like the sound from 83'-84' it is very distinct how Brent filled in with the band..very trippy!! Always some nice shows on the run to NYE..The Scarlet>Fire smokes in this solid 2nd set..so please..GIVE IT A WHIRL!! Forever Grateful>Forever Dead!!

A little off-timed at the end Seems like Jer wants to get right into Black Peter as you can hear the opening licks well before the end of Throwing Stones.  Black Peter was fabulous, but the transition into Sugar Mag was interesting, in that it sounded like it took quite a while to get into sync.  I wish I had been there.

Thanks for Posting I have an old Maxell IIS with the second set of this show that I love to listen to - I just don't know how many more times its going to play. It's funny because I had fallen into that FLAC or HiRes only music, but listening to my old tapes has made me realize how even mp3s of these shows, especially soundboard versions, are far better than what we used to listen to all the time.
Scarlet Fire Just wanted to say that this Scarlet Fire is a really enjoyable 30 minutes of music.  Thanks to all involved.
